4706|FINANCIAL IMPACTS OF NETWORKING AND RESOURCE SHARING.     LIBRARY COOPERATIVES WILL EVOLVE MORE INTO AUTOMATED LIBRARY NETWORKS WHICHARE GENERALLY MORE COST-EFFECTIVE, LESS LABOUR-INTENSIVE, AND PROVIDE MORE ANDBETTER SERVICE. THE MORE SUCCESSFUL US NETWORKS ARE THOSE WHERE THE MEMBERLIBRARIES HAVE A SIGNIFICANT COMMITMENT WITH FUNDS FROM THEIR LOCAL LIBRARIES'OPERATING BUDGETS AND WHICH VIEW THE SERVICES AS AN INTEGRAL PART OF THEIRESSENTIAL OPERATIONS. COST-EFFECTIVE NETWORKS ARE CHARACTERISED BY GREATERCOMPETITION, LESS STATE AND FEDERAL CONTROL, AND MORE RESEARCH ANDDEVELOPMENT. THE NETWORK'S ECONOMIC REVOLUTION FOR PUBLIC LIBRARIES ISBEGINNING TO OCCUR WHERE AUTOMATED NETWORKS HAVE EXTENDED SERVICES DIRECTLY TOTHE USERS IN THEIR HOMES.
