4735|LIFE STYLE RESEARCH' AN AID TO PROMOTING PUBLIC LIBRARIES.     DESCRIBES A LIFE STYLE RESEARCH STUDY OF 423| RESIDENTS AGED 25|-64| IN THE5|-COUNTY METROPOLITAN AREA OF COLUMBUS, OHIO, COMMISSIONED BY THE GREAT TRAIBBROADCASTING COMPANY TO GAIN A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF ITS RADIO AUDIENCE. THEDATA, ANALYSED BY OCLC, SUGGESTS AN APPROACH TO LIBRARY USE PROMOTION THATEXPRESSIVELY DEMONSTRATES HOW LIBRARY SERVICES CAN FIT INTO PREEXISTING NEEDSAND INTERESTS. THE PUBLIC SHOULD BE SHOWN HOW LIBRARY SERVICES CAN HELP TOSOLVE REAL LIFE PROBLEMS. THE LIFE STYLE VARIABLES CAN HELP PINPOINT THESEPROBLEMS AND SUGGEST PROMOTIONAL THEMES AND IDEAS.
