4802|SPECIAL DOCUMENTATION SERVICES: 2| PRACTICAL EXAMPLES.     IN MAY 78| THE PROVINCIAL CENTRAL LIBRARY OF LIMBURG IN THE NETHERLANDS CREATEDA CURRENT AND SOCIAL AFFAIRS INFORMATION SERVICE FOR PUBLIC LIBRARIES IN THEREGION. AT THE CENTRAL LIBRARY A TEAM OF 2| STAFF SCAN 5| NATIONAL AND ALL LOCALNEWSPAPERS TOGETHER WITH A NUMBER OF JOURNALS OF LOCAL INTEREST FOR ARTICLESAND INFORMATION RELATING TO LIMBURG. THE INFORMATION EXTRACTED FROM THESESOURCES IS CLASSIFIED INTO 75| SUBJECT FIELDS COVERING THE SOCIAL, CULTURAL ANDPOLITICAL LIFE OF THE PROVINCE, AND AT PRESENT 57| LIBRARIES SUBSCRIBE TO THISSERVICE. IN THE NAARDEN-BUSSUM CENTRAL PUBLIC LIBRARY IN THE NETHERLANDS ASIMILAR SERVICE WAS FORMED IN OCT 79| RELATING TO EMPLOYMENT AND TRAININGOPPORTUNITIES. DUE TO LACK OF FUNDS THE SERVICE IS ORGANISED BY AN UNPAID,VOLUNTARY ASSISTANT.
